# Service Status Monitoring Endpoint Configuration

## Background

We have developed a Spring Boot application with an endpoint that retrieves the current system time. We would like to use Spring Boot Actuator to monitor whether this system is running properly.

## Requirements

Please write the `application.properties` configuration file so that the web application can start normally and the service health can be monitored.

## Technology Stack

["Java 8+", "Spring Boot Actuator"]

## Implementation Requirements

- Configuration file name: `application.properties`
- Configuration file path: `src/main/resources`
- Add a port configuration to ensure the web service starts correctly
- Add Spring Boot Actuator configuration to enable service health monitoring
- No security vulnerabilities

## Existing File Contents

- `src/main/java/com/example/core/controller/DateController.java`
```java
package com.example.core.controller;

import org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;

import java.text.SimpleDateFormat;
import java.util.Date;

@RestController
public class DateController {
    @RequestMapping("/date")
    public String date(){
        SimpleDateFormat simpleDateFormat = new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd 'at' HH:mm:ss z");
        Date date = new Date(System.currentTimeMillis());
        return simpleDateFormat.format(date);
    }
}
```
- `src/main/java/com/example/core/Application.java`
```java
package com.example.core;

import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;
import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;

/**
 * Main application class to start the Spring Boot service.
 */
@SpringBootApplication
public class Application {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(Application.class, args);
    }

}
```

